      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PINKY ROCKS (7) led throughout to score two back then drifted back and missed the frame latest finishing a 11 length 6th at Angle Park (20.34). Can make amends. VICTA WALLY (8) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 4.5 lengths back in third (25.87) at this track in a Grade 6 over 455m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Expecting another good run. OUR BEAVER (2) was prominent throughout when winning in one of the fastest times of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 3.5 lengths at Angle Park (34.97). Must be included in calculations. FINNISS HONOUR (1) was a surprise last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
